CASSANDRA
=========

NoSql Distributed column based database which is highly performant
Highly scalable
AP system
separate cluster
decentralised p2p architecture 
for communication among themselves they use gossip protocol
No down time; highly available
CQL

Data fetching:
	Client asks for data to one of the nodes.
	Tunabe consistency:
		return result if 1 node has result (default)
		return result if 3 nodes agree on the result (quorum)
		return result if all nodes agree on the result (all nodes)
	The node checks the requested data in 1(default),2,3,... nodes and returns it
